Two separate issues:

**1. `StaticResource` doesn't update at runtime.** Use `DynamicResource` instead — it re-evaluates when the underlying resource changes:

```xml
<!-- ❌ Won't update -->
<Label TextColor="{StaticResource PrimaryTextColor}" />

<!-- ✅ Updates when you swap the ResourceDictionary -->
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryTextColor}" />
```

Then swap themes by replacing the merged dictionary at runtime:

```csharp
var mergedDicts = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
mergedDicts.Clear();
mergedDicts.Add(new DarkTheme()); // or LightTheme
```

**2. Android restarts the Activity on UI mode change.** Add `ConfigChanges` to your `MainActivity` so Android doesn't recreate it:

```csharp
[Activity(
    Theme = "@style/Maui.SplashTheme",
    ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.UiMode
        | ConfigChanges.ScreenSize
        | ConfigChanges.Orientation
        // ...other flags you already have
)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
}
```

Then detect the system change and apply your theme:

```csharp
public override void OnConfigurationChanged(Configuration newConfig)
{
    base.OnConfigurationChanged(newConfig);

    bool isDark = (newConfig.UiMode & UiMode.NightMask) == UiMode.NightYes;
    var mergedDicts = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
    mergedDicts.Clear();
    mergedDicts.Add(isDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
}
```

**TL;DR:** `StaticResource` → `DynamicResource` for runtime updates; `ConfigChanges.UiMode` on `MainActivity` to prevent the restart.
